data.text:
Andy Frasco & The U.N.

FIRE STAGE 7 P.M.

Known for their kaleidoscopic musical fusion and audacious stage presence, Andy Frasco and the U.N. bring an unforgettable performance of funk, jazz, surf rock, blues, and more.

Spafford

ICE STAGE 4:30 P.M.

Rock, funk, jazz, reggae, electro-pop, Spafford can do it all, bringing an improvisational flair to every moment onstage.

Deadphish Orchestra

FIRE STAGE 5:15 P.M.

Two great flavors that are even better together. DeadPhish Orchestra interprets the music of the Grateful Dead and Phish, giving jam band fans everything they’re looking for, and more.

The Sweet Lillies

FIRE STAGE 3:45 P.M.

With guitar, viola, and upright bass given flight by ethereal, vocal harmonies, the Sweet Lillies' music has an old-time soul with a forward-looking eye.

A-Mac & The Height

ICE STAGE 2:45 P.M.

This energetic Denver, CO-based five-piece has a charismatic approach fueled by conscious thinking, with lyrics that are uplifting, relatable and insightful.

The Jauntee

FIRE STAGE 2:15 P.M.

Formed in 2010, this Colorado band pushes the boundaries of improvisational music, combining elements of jazz, funk, rock, and psychedelic jams.

Eminence Ensemble

ICE STAGE 1:15 P.M.

Making complex-yet-digestible music, Eminence Ensemble bridges the gap between the jam-band and more traditional music scenes.

Chain Station

FIRE STAGE 1 P.M.

Vibe to the sound of this four-piece, high-energy, get 'em out on the dance floor string band from Colorado.

Lucid Vision

OUTDOOR STAGE 6:15 P.M.

Spreading light through sound, the Denver-based Lucid Vision brings listeners to a melodic realm of electronic genre bends.

Future Joy

OUTDOOR STAGE 2:30 P.M.

With a fusion of live electronic beats and soulful sax, this dynamic duo serves up an unforgettable mix of soul and funk.
